/us/florida-influencer-with-no-right-hand-gets-ticket-for-using-phone-in-right-hand-while-driving/articleshow/131373611.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/florida-influencer-with-no-right-hand-gets-ticket-for-using-phone-in-right-hand-while-driving/articleshow/131373611.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-28T21:40:08+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131373818,imgsize-130232.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Gulf of suspicion: US and Iran said to be nearing deal even as missiles fly]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131373522.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Amidst escalating tensions and attacks in the Strait of Hormuz, the US and Iran are reportedly nearing a diplomatic breakthrough. A draft Memorandum of Understanding could extend a fragile ceasefire, opening a 60-day window for talks on Iran's nuclear program in exchange for economic relief.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/gulf-of-suspicion-us-and-iran-said-to-be-nearing-deal-even-as-missiles-fly/articleshow/131373522.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/gulf-of-suspicion-us-and-iran-said-to-be-nearing-deal-even-as-missiles-fly/articleshow/131373522.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-28T21:28:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Chidanand Rajghatta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131373604,imgsize-1262817.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[DOWN THE RABBIT HOLE: Bangladeshi buffalo 'Donald Trump' pardoned – a brief history of animal sacrifices]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131372349.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[We live in the era of viral animals, from Larry the Cat, the permanent fixture at 10 Downing Street, to Moo Deng, the cute pygmy hippo in Thailand, and Punch, the lonely monkey whose inability to make friends made the world go aww. Donald Trump the buffalo might be the latest addition to this pantheon. But long before the algorithm turned animals into celebrities, humans were already turning them into gods, omens, sacrifices, scapegoats and pardoned prisoners.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/down-the-rabbit-hole-bangladeshi-buffalo-donald-trump-pardoned-a-brief-history-of-animal-sacrifices/articleshow/131372349.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/down-the-rabbit-hole-bangladeshi-buffalo-donald-trump-pardoned-a-brief-history-of-animal-sacrifices/articleshow/131372349.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-28T20:28:25+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Nirmalya Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131372845,imgsize-99160.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[He would never harm himself: Suchir Balaji's parents say they are not giving up, Elon Musk responds]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131372708.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-would-never-harm-himself-suchir-balajis-parents-say-they-are-not-giving-up-elon-musk-responds/articleshow/131372708.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-would-never-harm-himself-suchir-balajis-parents-say-they-are-not-giving-up-elon-musk-responds/articleshow/131372708.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-28T20:19:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="i